        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 24 at 7:03AM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 703 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Esperanza, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Hancock, Esperanza, Finlay, McNary, and Round Top Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
